          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What is the difference between Kartra and WebinarJam?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Kartra is an all-in-one marketing platform that includes pages, email, memberships, and checkout. WebinarJam is a dedicated live webinar platform. Genesis Digital owns both, and they integrate tightly — you can host webinars through WebinarJam and manage the entire funnel, follow-up, and checkout through Kartra without third-party tools.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How much does Kartra cost in 2025?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Kartra offers several pricing tiers starting at $119/month for the Starter plan, which includes up to 2,500 contacts and core features. Higher-tier plans range up to $549/month and unlock more contacts, team members, and advanced features. They frequently offer a $1 trial for 14 or 30 days so you can test before committing.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Can Kartra replace my email marketing tool and page builder?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Yes. Kartra includes a drag-and-drop page builder with templates for sales pages, opt-ins, and thank-you pages, plus a full email marketing system with automation sequences, tagging, and segmentation. Most users who switch from separate tools like Mailchimp plus Leadpages report that Kartra covers both use cases while adding features like integrated checkout and membership delivery.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      }
